HEADWORD: Imputative
<hw>Im*put"a*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>imputativus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>imputatif</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Transferred by imputation; that may be imputed.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Im*put"a*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Actual righteousness as well as <qex>imputative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Warburton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impute</ent>⟦br⟧
